job.plain_text_description:
We govern the beautiful game and ensure it's run with transparency and integrity.
Join our team in Miami and support us on our mission.

These are your key tasks:

- Conducting autonomously ethics proceedings in accordance with the FIFA Code of Ethics;
- Investigating ethics proceedings, including the review and analysis of financial records, the use of forensic audit techniques, and the development of financial investigative strategies;
- Drafting communications and request for information to the interested/accused parties within an ethics proceeding;
- Supporting the preparation of witness interviews and witness statements, and, when necessary, coordinating such tasks with other departments or external experts within the context of ethics proceedings;
- Liaising with FIFA departments and subject-matter experts to secure support for FIFA Ethics Committee matters;
- Supporting the relevant chairperson and members of the Ethics Committee by preparing case files, legal analyses, and draft decisions to facilitate effective deliberations;
- Assisting the relevant chairperson of the FIFA Ethics Committee in the preparation of meetings;
- Assessment of legal aid requests, witness protection, witness/victim’s psychological support, and when necessary, coordinating such tasks with other departments or external experts within the ethics proceedings;
- Drafting final Reports within an ethics proceeding;
- Analyzing testimonials and other documentary evidence, including financial and audit records, to weigh its credibility and probative value within the context and standards of the FIFA Code of Ethics;
- Conduct legal analysis of FIFA precedent and CAS jurisprudence to support the drafting of final investigation reports and Ethics Committee decisions;
- Drafting decisions of the Adjudicatory Chamber;
- Contributing to the ongoing development of workflows, templates, and best practices to ensure efficiency and consistency;
- Identify and recommend measures to prevent violations of the FIFA Code of Ethics and promote the safeguarding and integrity of football worldwide;
- Close collaboration and support to the Head of Department in creating efficient ethics proceedings (i.e. determining processes, workflow, template creation, etc.);
- Ensuring a worldwide recognition of the activity of the Investigation Department and the Judicial Bodies Subdivision;
- Assistance in preparing any report related to the activities of the ethics department, including newsletters, status reports, etc.
- Holding and participating in workshops with FIFA employees, member associations or confederations on Judicial Bodies-related issues.

We work hard at FIFA.
We are dedicated, ambitious and innovative.

And we respect our values. Always.

For all roles, we seek talented people with an entrepreneurial spirit and a global mindset.

The specific competencies we require for this position are:

- Excellent legal drafting and presentation skills in English;
- Proficiency legal drafting in Spanish or French is an asset;
- Good knowledge of football governance as well as of FIFA’s regulations, and proven experience in FIFA’s Disciplinary and Ethics proceedings;
- Ability to conduct analysis and draw out conclusions;
- Strong ability to analyze financial data, audit findings, and forensic accounting reports to detect and understand irregularities;
- Excellent editorial skills;
- Good planning and organisational skills;
- Solid IT-know how;
- Ability to work unsupervised and precisely;
- Ability to work well under pressure and to respect deadlines;
- Good analytical skills;
- Conscientiousness, accuracy and quality;
- Punctuality;
- Proactive approach;
- Rigorous and consistent, particularly when handling large amounts of documents;
- Team player with good interpersonal relations;
- Excellent communication skills;
- Cooperative and team-oriented mindset, fostering transparent communication and knowledge sharing;
- Motivated, autodidact, dynamic and proactive personality;
- Ability to adapt to changing priorities;
- Agility;
- Ability to adapt to an international and multicultural environment;
- Pleasant and empathetic;
- Law University degree (Bar Exam);
- Post-Graduate in Sport law is an asset;
- Training or certification in white-collar investigations (including forensic accounting, CPA, CFE, etc.) or prior experience in an audit firm is an asset;
- Minimum 6-8 years of experience in similar positions, dealing with disciplinary and ethics regulations matters in a sports governing body;
- Experience handling cases of misappropriation of funds, bribery and corruption, and working alongside compliance, finance teams, or external auditors, is a strong asset;
- Native/C2 in English;
- Proficiency in any other FIFA language (F / ES) is an asset;
- Proficient in Word / PowerPoint / Excel/Jira;
- Ability to leverage AI tools to enhance investigative efficiency while ensuring accuracy, confidentiality, and compliance with applicable legal and ethical standards.

The biggest benefit of a career at FIFA is the privilege to work for the beautiful game and create something that matters.

Alongside that privilege, we also offer some extra perks and benefits:

Health insurance: We offer generous medical, vision, and dental insurance coverage.

Continuous learning: We care about your development and encourage internal mobility, offering a variety of training and education to help achieve it.

Retirement: We offer generous 401(k) employer contributions.

Vacation: Maintain a healthy work/life balance with a generous vacation allowance.

job.html_description:
 Fulham FC Foundation are currently seeking to recruit an enthusiastic and committed person to take up the casual position of a Female Football Coach.<br><br>Reporting directly to our Operations Officers the Female Football Coach will be responsible for managing a number of female teams at one of the foundations partner schools. This role would involve both the management of these teams, as well as providing high-quality, team-based training sessions throughout the week. You will also be responsible for overseeing any fixtures these team have across the season. This is a casual role where flexibility is essential, as the delivery of training sessions and fixtures changes across the school term.&nbsp;<br><br>The successful candidate will be somebody who has prior experience managing a female team, and holds at least a UEFA C License qualification. Due to the requirements stipulated by the school, the successful candidate will be a female coach with relatable experience to their players allowing them to be a positive role model to them.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Although this role is casual, with the hours varying across the season, meaning that there is no set timetable. There are some key times when training sessions and fixtures are likely to happen. Therefore, the ideal candidate will have good availability during the afternoons of the working week. The ideal availability will be:<br>Monday – Friday from 2pm to 6pm<br><br>There will also be opportunity to work across other foundation programmes such as our ‘Player Development Centres’ and ‘Girls Development Centres’ should the successful candidate want to.&nbsp;<br><br>Whilst there is no obligation for Fulham FC Foundation to provide, or for the Female Football Coaches to accept, work. Female Football Coaches who do not work for an extended period of time (3 months), may no longer be offered work. &nbsp;<br><br>Salary: £16.50 p/h<br><br>Next steps:&nbsp;<br>The closing date for this role is the 30th of June, however applications will be reviewed consistently so any appropriate candidate may be interviewed before this date. &nbsp;<br><strong><br>If successful, you will join a vibrant team who are passionate about achieving the organisation's vision of “an active healthy, inclusive and thriving community”, and you’ll have the opportunity to build on your existing skills through a variety of training and development opportunities and experiences. This role will also play a role in supporting the Foundation’s Women’s and Girls Strategy to develop and support opportunities for underrepresented groups.&nbsp;</strong><br><strong><br>*This job description should not be regarded as exclusive or exhaustive. It is intended as an outline indication of areas of activity and responsibility and will be amended in the light of the changing needs of the organisation.</strong><br><br><br>
<h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul id="isPasted"><li>To act as an Ambassador for Fulham FC Foundation (FFCF), representing the organisation professionally in line with its values.&nbsp;</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><ul><li>To design and deliver high quality, team training sessions to the teams you’ll be working with.</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><ul><li>To manage the teams during both home and away fixtures, including all the team admin that does along with managing the team.&nbsp;</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><ul><li>To provide high-quality, individualised feedback to each of the players in your teams to support their footballing development.&nbsp;</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><ul><li>To be a positive role model to the student athletes, helping both motivate and support them with their football, and education.</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><ul><li>To identify and support progression pathways for talented young people.&nbsp;</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><ul><li>To provide a safe, positive and inclusive learning environment at all times,</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><ul><li>To adhere to FFCF’s safeguarding policies and procedures, ensuring the timely reporting of any safeguarding concerns or incidents within sessions.&nbsp;</li></ul>&nbsp;
<h3>Requirements</h3>Essential:&nbsp;<br><br id="isPasted">Experience:&nbsp;<br><ul><li>Experience of delivering high quality training sessions to female footballers.</li><li>Experience of running a 9 or 11 aside female football team.</li><li>Experience of working with others as part of a coaching team.</li><li>Has a driving license and/or is willing to travel independently.</li></ul>&nbsp;<br>Skills, Knowledge &amp; Qualifications:<br><ul><li>Excellent verbal communication skills.</li><li>Excellent knowledge of Women’s Football.</li><li>Excellent knowledge of the pathway opportunities for female players.</li><li>First Aid, Safeguarding and DBS qualification.</li><li>A UEFA C Coaching Qualification, or currently undertaking and due to complete this year.&nbsp;</li><li>Base knowledge of and willingness to learn &amp; contribute towards FFCF strategic aims.&nbsp;</li></ul><br>Personal Qualities:<br><ul><li>A positive role-model for children &amp; young people.</li><li>Ability to travel independently across Surrey and South-West London, including transport of equipment.</li><li>Well presented, with a professional manner.</li><li>Positive, energetic persona. Able to build rapport with participants.</li><li>Excellent time-keeping &amp; punctuality.</li><li>Willingness to learn &amp; develop personally &amp; professionally.</li></ul><br>Preferred:&nbsp;<br id="isPasted">Experience:&nbsp;<br><ul><li>Experience of delivering football sessions in a secondary school</li><li>Experience of working with high performing footballers.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience of leading a local female grassroots team</li></ul>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Skills, Knowledge &amp; Qualifications:<br><ul><li>Additional football qualifications such as Goalkeeping, S&amp;C, or Fitness.</li><li>Knowledge and links to local grassroots football teams.</li><li>UEFA B License (or willing to work towards)</li></ul>&nbsp;<br><br>

 Fulham FC Foundation are currently seeking to recruit an enthusiastic and committed person to take up the casual position of DisAbility Football &amp; Sports Coach.<br><br id="isPasted">Reporting directly to our Senior DisAbility Development Manager, the DisAbility Football &amp; Sports Coaches are responsible for delivering high-quality football &amp; sports coaching to children, young people and adults with disabilities and additional needs. This role involves delivery across a wide-range of our DisAbility Programmes, including Pan DisAbility Clubs, Active Autism, Down’s Syndrome ‘Badgers’, Blind and Partially Sighted, Cerebral Palsy and Dwarfism Football Sessions. In addition there will be opportunities to work in our DisAbility Schools programme delivering PE, Enrichment Activities and After School Clubs.<br><br>While the primary focus of this role is on DisAbility Football &amp; Sport, there may be opportunities to contribute to other FFC Foundation activities such as Skills Club, Development Centres, Soccer Schools, Primary Education, Kicks, and Health &amp; Wellbeing. We would encourage candidates to prioritise DisAbility Programmes where possible, while remaining flexible to support other areas as needed.<br><br>This is a casual role where flexibility is essential, as the role necessitates involvement in supporting the delivery of programme activities as and when required. &nbsp;<br><br>The successful candidate will be somebody who has prior experience delivering football &amp; sports coaching sessions to children &amp; young people with disabilities or additional needs in grassroots &amp; school settings, holds at least a FA Level 1/Introduction to Coaching Football qualification and is committed to the charitable purpose of Fulham FC Foundation.<br><br>As this role is casual, there is no set timetable. Sessions may be offered on an adhoc or regular basis, depending on the needs of Fulham FC Foundation. It is the responsibility of the DisAbility Football &amp; Sports Coaches to maintain consistent and effective communication with our Senior DisAbility Development Manager and Operations Officers to ensure the continuation of work.<br><br>Whilst there is no obligation for Fulham FC Foundation to provide, or for the DisAbility Football &amp; Sports Coaches to accept, work. DisAbility Football &amp; Sports Coaches who do not work for an extended period of time, will be deactivated.<br><br>The successful candidates should be available to work across at least one of the below times, in order to receive work. We are extremely keen to hear from those who are able to work on Saturday mornings.<br><br>Weekdays – 9am to 5 pm;<br>Weekday Evenings – 5pm to 9pm<br>Weekends – Saturdays – 8am to 12noon.<br>Work in other timings is available, however on a far reduced frequency.<br>Salary Range: £12.95 p/h to £16.50 p/h<br><br><strong>Next steps</strong>:<br>There is no closing date for this role. Applications will be reviewed on a bi-weekly basis.<br><br><strong id="isPasted">If successful, you will join a vibrant team who are passionate about achieving the organisation's vision of “an active, inclusive and thriving community”, and you’ll have the opportunity to build on your existing skills through a variety of training and development opportunities and experiences</strong><br>*<strong>This job description should not be regarded as exclusive or exhaustive. It is intended as an outline indication of areas of activity and responsibility and will be amended in the light of the changing needs of the organisation</strong>.
<h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul id="isPasted"><li>To act as an Ambassador for Fulham FC Foundation (FFCF), representing the organisation professionally in line with its values.</li><li>To plan and deliver high-quality football and sports coaching sessions to children, young people &amp; adults in-line with FFCF standards.</li><li>To provide a safe, positive and inclusive learning environment at all times,</li><li>To adhere to FFCF’s safeguarding policies and procedures, ensuring the timely reporting of any safeguarding concerns or incidents within sessions.</li><li>To engage, include, inspire and grow participation across FFCF activities.</li><li>To support the transition of participants between different FFCF programmes and activities.</li><li>To champion opportunities for individuals from underrepresented groups within FFCF activities.&nbsp;</li><li>To identify and support progression pathways for talented young people.&nbsp;</li><li>To support the development of FFCF programmes through positive collaboration with Department Managers / Operations Officers.&nbsp;</li><li>To support the promotion of FFCF programmes across the local community.</li><li>&nbsp;To assist in data collection and completion of monitoring &amp; evaluation on an ongoing basis.</li></ul>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;
<h3>Requirements</h3>Essential:<br id="isPasted">Experience:<br><ul><li>Delivery of football coaching sessions in a grassroots environment</li><li>Delivery of sports coaching sessions to children, young people or adults with disabilities and additional needs.</li><li>Delivery within a school/college setting.</li><li>Working in a customer-facing role.</li></ul><br>Skills, Knowledge &amp; Qualifications:<br><ul><li>Introduction to Coaching Football qualification</li><li>In-date FA Emergency First Aid</li><li>In-date FA Safeguarding Children certificate</li><li>Base knowledge of and willingness to learn &amp; contribute towards FFCF strategic aims.</li></ul><br>Personal Qualities:<br><ul><li>A positive role-model for children &amp; young people.</li><li>Ability to travel independently across South-West London, including transport of equipment.</li><li>Well presented, with a professional manner.</li><li>Positive, energetic persona. Able to build rapport with participants.</li><li>Excellent time-keeping &amp; punctuality.</li><li>Willingness to learn &amp; develop personally &amp; professionally.</li></ul><br>Preferred:<br>Experience:<br><ul><li>Delivery of football &amp; sports coaching sessions in a Club Community Organisation (CCO).</li><li>Delivery of Physical Education within a school setting.</li><li>Delivery within a classroom environment.</li><li>Marketing &amp; Promoting participation activities in the community.</li><li>Delivery of football &amp; sports coaching sessions to females.</li></ul><br>Skills, Knowledge &amp; Qualifications:<br><ul><li>FA Level 2/UEFA C in Coaching Football qualification (or higher).</li><li>Additional PE/HLTA qualification</li><li>Mentoring qualification</li><li>Non-football NGB sports qualifications.</li></ul>

 In this role, you will work as part of the Ticket Office team at Craven Cottage to manage inbound enquiries across a number of different communication channels – phone, email, online and in person – and deliver on the sale of commercial products relating to Fulham Football Club through the Club’s ticketing system, Ticketmaster. &nbsp;<br id="isPasted">&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>The Ticket Office team form a critical part of the sales structure of the business, and you will be required to proactively support the Club in its objective to make it easy for people to buy from Fulham FC by assisting with supporter queries on our busy matchdays. &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>You will form part of the team working as the first line of contact for our fans’ inquiries and as such we expect a high level of customer service and support at all times. &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>You will be asked to provide assistance to the Head of Ticketing and the Deputy Supporter Centre Manager with a variety of Ticket Office duties as required. A good level of communication will be required. &nbsp;
<h3>Responsibilities</h3><strong>The Ticketing and Membership Executive - Match Days must have:&nbsp;</strong><ul><li>Customer Service experience</li><li>A good IT and technology systems understanding</li><li>Competent with all Microsoft Office Products</li><li>Ability to deal with the public with a focus on service excellence&nbsp;</li><li>Able to work under pressure&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to communicate with and relate to staff members at all levels&nbsp;</li><li>Work on own initiative / creative&nbsp;</li><li>Respect for confidentiality&nbsp;</li><li>Flexible attitude to work tasks&nbsp;</li><li>Genuine commitment to provide high quality customer service&nbsp;</li><li>Positive ‘can do’ approach&nbsp;</li><li>Desire to learn with enthusiasm</li></ul><br><strong>Ideally, The Ticketing and Membership Executive - Match Days will have:&nbsp;</strong><ul><li>Previous experience with Ticketing Systems</li><li>Experience in a sales role</li></ul>
<h3>Requirements</h3><strong>The following is a non-exhaustive list of the responsibilities of the role:&nbsp;</strong><ul><li>Providing service excellence when dealing with the Clubs customers (supporters, staff etc), at all times, serving customers in a polite, courteous and professional manner &nbsp;</li><li>Handling any customer queries and complaints with a solution driven and positive approach &nbsp;</li><li>Processing all ticket sales for Fulham FC products, away games and supporter travel, with daily reconciliation of all sales through the Ticketmaster system &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Updating and maintaining supporter database records to ensure data is accurately captured across the Ticketing System (Ticketmaster) and CRM System &nbsp;</li><li>This role will be required to work all home league matchdays – on evenings or weekends , and an other ad-hoc fixtures or events as required &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>You may also be required to carry out other tasks, not listed, to assist in the efficient operation of our business. &nbsp;At all times you will be required to act in accordance with FFC company policies, follow departmental procedures and maintain the highest level of confidentiality. &nbsp;<strong><br></strong></li></ul>

 Fulham FC Foundation is seeking a creative part-time Graphic Designer to support the communications of Fulham FC’s official charity. This role will work across a wide range of digital and print design projects, helping to bring the Foundation’s visual identity to life across all programmes and activities.<br><br>Working within established brand guidelines, you will contribute to digital campaigns and front‑end design projects, while also bringing your own creativity and ideas to each brief. Design direction will be provided, but the ability to work independently will be key to success in this role.<br><br>If you are passionate about design, looking for a new challenge, and feel you can add value to our team, please visit hhtp://careers.fulhamfc.com/<br>&nbsp;<br><em>*This job description should not be regarded as exclusive or exhaustive. It is intended as an outline indication of areas of activity and responsibility and will be amended in the light of the changing needs of the organisation</em>.<br><br>Closing date for applications is Wednesday 5 August 2026.<br><br>Salary range: £20k-£22.5k<br>&nbsp;<br>First stage interviews will take place across Thursday 13th &amp; Friday 14th August 2026, and second stage interviews will take place on Thursday 20th August 2026. Please ensure you are available to interview on these dates prior to applying.<br><br>The post is subject to an enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service check.<br><br>Fulham Football Club Foundation is committed to increasing diversity and maintaining an inclusive workplace culture. We welcome applications from all qualified candidates regardless of ethnicity, race, gender, religious belief, sexual orientation, age, marital status, or disability.<br><br>Applicants must have the right to live and work in the United Kingdom and be able to provide appropriate documentation for the duration of their employment.<br><br><br>
<h3>Responsibilities</h3>Your responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:<br><br>• Designing and building digital assets, including social media graphics, flyers, presentations, and newsletters<br>• Implementing design briefs in line with the Foundation’s brand guidelines<br>• Supporting and contributing to the development of the Foundation’s visual identity across multiple platforms and mediums<br>• Managing multiple design briefs from concept through to final delivery<br>• Working to tight deadlines while following efficient resourcing and scheduling processes<br>• Supporting social media scheduling and posting across Foundation channels<br>• Assisting with asset management and the printing of marketing collateral
<h3>Requirements</h3><strong>The successful candidate will:</strong><br>• Be able to manage multiple briefs and work under pressure to tight deadlines<br>• Demonstrate a strong portfolio showcasing a range of print and digital design work for varied audiences<br>• Have advanced working knowledge of Adobe Creative Suite, including Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign, as well as PowerPoint<br>• Hold a design‑related degree, or demonstrate equivalent experience through a strong portfolio<br>• Ideally have experience working within sport, community, or charitable organisations<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Personal attributes</strong><br>We are looking for a team player who is:<br>• Open to feedback and able to collaborate effectively<br>• Highly organised with strong attention to detail<br>• Able to problem‑solve independently<br>• Capable of blending creative vision with strategic thinking<br>• Values in-person collaboration and team culture (the role is office based)<br>&nbsp;

job.plain_text_description:
Envie de rejoindre un Groupe unique et ambitieux ?

Grâce à un modèle économique articulé autour du football masculin et ouvert sur l'international, Eagle Football Group, propriétaire de l'Olympique Lyonnais se démarque dans le paysage français du sport professionnel.

Propriétaire de notre Stade, nous avons à cœur de respecter les enjeux socio-économiques tout en étant un acteur responsable et engagé dans la vie locale.

Notre dynamisme incarné par notre équipe masculine et notre Academy mixte nous incite à innover sans cesse et à nous adapter aux profonds changements de notre coeur de métier.

Nous recherchons un(e) Juriste (H/F) en CDD de remplacement à pourvoir dès à présent.

Vous serez rattaché(e) à la Direction Juridique, sous la responsabilité de la Responsable Juridique.

Véritable acteur de la sécurisation juridique des activités du Groupe, vous intervenez sur un périmètre varié couvrant la gestion des assurances, les contrats commerciaux et techniques, ainsi que le suivi des contentieux.

Votre objectif sera donc de protéger et d'accompagner le développement du Groupe en assurant le pilotage des contrats d'assurance et des sinistres, la rédaction et la négociation des contrats liés à l'exploitation des infrastructures, ainsi que la gestion des pré-contentieux et de la veille juridique.

Dans ce cadre, vos missions seront les suivantes :

- Assurances

- Suivi des contrats d’assurance Groupe (RC, multirisques, cyber, construction flotte auto…) ;
- Lancement et suivi des appels d’offres, revue et négociation des polices ;
- Souscription de nouveaux contrats selon les besoins opérationnels ;
- Déclarations et suivi des sinistres en lien avec les services internes et les assureurs.

- Contrats commerciaux

- Rédaction, révision et négociation de contrats en particulier : contrats techniques en lien avec la gestion des infrastructures, tels que des contrats de prestations de services, contrats d’exploitation/maintenance, baux, NDA… ;
- Suivi de l’exécution des contrats en coordination avec les équipes métiers, gestion des relations contractuelles et des renouvellements.

- Contentieux et veille juridique

- Préparation des mises en demeure, rédaction de protocoles transactionnels ;
- Suivi des pré-contentieux et contentieux en lien avec le périmètre d’activités ;
- Veille juridique et réglementaire en droit des affaires et des assurances.

- Support transversal

- Participation aux projets juridiques du Groupe ;
- Actualisation des ressources documentaires.

PROFIL:

Vous justifiez d’un Bac +5 (Droit des Assurances ou Droit des Affaires) et d’une expérience de 5 à 10 ans en entreprise, cabinet ou courtage, avec une forte composante commerciale.

Nous recherchons les compétences techniques suivantes :

- Maîtrise du droit des assurances et du droit des contrats ;
- Excellentes capacités rédactionnelles et de négociation ;
- Maîtrise des outils bureautiques (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) ;
- Appétence pour les outils digitaux de gestion contractuelle et IA juridique ;
- Anglais juridique courant (écrit et oral).

Nous apprécierons également vos qualités personnelles telles que votre agilité intellectuelle, votre esprit d’analyse et de synthèse ainsi que votre sens du relationnel et du travail en équipe, permettant de vous adapter à des environnements/métiers divers et d’avoir une véritable orientation business.

Tous les postes sont ouverts aux personnes en situation de handicap.

Pour vous donner un avant-goût de votre quotidien parmi nous, voici quelques-uns de nos avantages :

- Une vraie qualité de vie au travail, au cœur de notre politique RH (partenariat avec une salle de sport à proximité des bureaux, nombreux évènements conviviaux organisés tout au long de l’année, une assistance sociale à votre disposition) ;
- Un parcours d’intégration unique ;
- La possibilité de s’impliquer dans des actions sociales et solidaires.

Convaincu(e) ? N’hésitez plus, postulez !
